      <br>
 You enter the two story structure of the Tavern known as The Blood. As you enter many faces turn and stare at you.<br>
To your left you see three coldain playing cards with a robed Teir'Dal lady. To the right you see a human in full plate, a strong jaw and long black hair. This man seems powerful but he travels with a gnome in a dark robe. The gnome seems to be carrying a book made of iron and a silver skull carved on the front. The two are having a drink of the House ale, Blood Wine.<br>
At the bar five faces met your gaze. One troll in stinky leather armor, and he seems to have some sort of spiked whip at his side. A middle aged male halfling with curly blonde hair, nice studded leather and expensive looking daggers attached to his deathfist emblazoned belt.<br>
Another human, this one in chainmail and bearing the creast of Hate on his black silk cape. <br>
A hooded female figure is the forth face that meets your gaze. All you can see is she has some sort of elven features in this low candle-lit room.<br>
The fifth person to look upon you at the bar seems to be a ogre of great strength. He wields of large blade mounted on his back. He also has many blades attached to his sword harness. He wears heavy silver full plate. He looks at you and gives a slight smile.<br>
You come to the edge of the bar and notice the bartender now. He was not noticable before with the troll in the way. The bartender asks you what you would like to drink. Your shocked it is a white-furred gnoll. He looks friendly enough though and you order a drink.<br>
<br>
You sit and have your drink for a time and then notice something strange that you had not seen before. A hallway to the right side of the bar. At the end you see a dark oak table with a curtain behind it. At the table there appears to be two chairs. One seems to be occupied by a shadowy cloaked figure.<br>
<br>
You are curious so you walk toward the table. As you get closer you hear a voice as soft as a whisper, but deep as a chasm. &quot;Greetings, please come and sit.&quot;<br>
<br>
You come closer and deside to take a seat. Under the hood you see two piercing red eyes. <br>
<br>
&quot;I understand you are new to this area?&quot; &quot;Perhaps I can assist thee.&quot;<br>
The man gives you a letter. <br>
<br>
&quot;Take this letter to a friend of mine and I shall reward you with a great treasure.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Be warned however, anyone but my friend that reads this note shall suffer under my wrath.&quot;<br>
<br>
You ask who this friend is...the reply...<br>
<br>
&quot;Banegrivm&quot;   Tell him a old friend is back...tell him he will understand once he reads the letter.<br>
<br>
You make your way out of the Tavern and into the cold night air of the Eastern Commonlands.<br>
<br>
*You stare at the letter in your hands* What to do next?<br>
<br>
<br>
  The Dark Assassin of Firiona Vie<br>
